{# PROOF: statement — the "we have no testimonials yet, and here is why" block.

   A pre-launch business has no case studies, and every visitor forms that
   objection inside the first ten seconds. On this site the answer to it —
   "we're pre-launch, so we lead with the process" plus "no fake testimonials,
   no borrowed case studies" — existed only as an h2 on the FOURTH nav item.
   Every other page left the reader silently wondering. This is the most
   trust-building claim the business owns and it belongs before the services
   grid.

   Every clone needs this in month one, which is exactly the case the variant
   library exists for.

   NO NEW CONFIG FIELDS, on purpose. It reads the process page's own heading
   and subhead, so the claim has ONE canonical home and cannot drift out of
   sync with the page it summarises. A client who wants different words edits
   the process copy, and both places follow.

   Rendered as a ruled statement on the page field rather than as a card, so
   it never reads as a badge or a testimonial widget. #}
{% set pp = site.pages.process %}
{% if pp and pp.heading %}
<div class="proof-none">
  <h3>{{ pp.heading }}</h3>
  <div>
    {% if pp.subhead %}<p>{{ pp.subhead }}</p>{% endif %}
    {% if pp.closing_note %}<p>{{ pp.closing_note }}</p>{% endif %}
  </div>
</div>
{% endif %}
